				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$X_{i} = \frac{{n_{{i,{\text{ in}}}} - { }n_{{i,{\text{ out}}}} }}{{n_{{i,{\text{ in}}}} }} = 1 - \frac{{n_{{i,{\text{ out}}}} }}{{n_{{i,{\text{ in}}}} }}.$$\end{document}

In general, the yield is defined as the amount of product(s) produced per amount of product(s) that could be produced:5Yp=np,out-np,innk,in·ukvp.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
