				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$Y_{{\text{p}}} = \frac{{n_{{{\text{p}},{\text{ out}}}} - { }n_{{{\text{p}},{\text{ in}}}} }}{{n_{{{\text{k}},{\text{ in}}}} }} \cdot \left| {\frac{{u_{{\text{k}}} }}{{v_{{\text{p}}} }}} \right| .$$\end{document}

The overall selectivity is defined as the amount of the reactant required to form a product per total amount of that reactant consumed:6Sp=np,out-np,innk,in-nk,out·ukvp.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
